==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hashish
<hw>Hash"ish</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(h⟦acr⟧sh"⟦emac⟧sh)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar.
<ets>hash⟦imac⟧sh</ets>.]</ety> <def>A slightly acrid gum resin produced
by the common hemp (<spn>Cannabis sativa</spn>), of the variety
<varn>Indica</varn>, when cultivated in a warm climate; also, the tops
of the plant, from which the resinous product is obtained. It is
narcotic, and has long been used in the East for its intoxicating
effect. The active psychoactive principle has been identified as
<part>tetrahydrocannabinol</part>. See <er>Bhang</er>, and
<er>Ganja</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hash.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

